<L N="265">&THORN;at &thorn;e fende hir hadde ouercomen</L>
<L>And out of hir penance ynomen;</L>
<L>And ful gode &yogh;eme he nam</L>
<L>It was &thorn;e fende &thorn;at wi&thorn; hir cam.</L>
<L>And seyd: "Eue, allas allas,</L>
<L N="270">Now is wers &thorn;an it was!</L>
<L>He &thorn;at come&thorn; in &thorn;i compeynie,</L>
<L>Now he ha&thorn; ygiled &thorn;e tvie:</L>
<L>For so&thorn;e, Eue, &thorn;at is he</L>
<L>&THORN;at giled &thorn;e to &thorn;e appel-tre</L>
<L N="275">And made &thorn;e wi&thorn; his enticement</L>
<L>To breke godes comandment".</L>
<L>&THORN;o Eue wist it was Satanas,</L>
<L>For sorwe &thorn;at in hir hert was</L>
<L>Sche swoned and fel to grounde,</L>
<L N="280">And lay stille a ful gode stounde;</L>
<L>And anon as sche awoke,</L>
<L>For drede of god sche lay and qwoke,</L>
<L>And seyd: "allas &mdash; &yogh;if god it wold &mdash;</L>
<L>&THORN;at euer was ich maked of mold!"</L>
<L N="285">Adam was in gret care</L>
<L>&THORN;at sey&yogh;e his wiif so iuel fare,</L>
<L>And seyd to &thorn;e fende of helle:</L>
<L>"Ich wald &thorn;at &thorn;ou wost me telle</L>
<L>Whi &thorn;ou inwest me and mi wiif</L>
<L N="290">And art about to pair our liif?</L>
<L>And we [did] &thorn;e neuer no dede</L>
<L>. . . . . stede".</L>
<L>&THORN;e fende answerd &thorn;o</L>
<L>And seyd: "Adam, &thorn;ou art mi fo.</L>
<L N="295">Sone after &thorn;e warld bigan</L>
<L>And god hadde fourmed &thorn;e to man,</L>
<L>Bi an angel he sent to me</L>
<L>&THORN;at y schuld anoure &thorn;e;</L>
<L>And (y) seyd: &thorn;at y nold,</L>
<L N="300">For, ar &thorn;ou wer maked of mold,</L>
<L>Ich was in heuen an angel bri&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Of grete pouwer and grete mi&yogh;t;</L>
<L>And for y nold anour &thorn;e nou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>In &thorn;is sorwe Icham ybrou&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="305">In to helle for to wende</L>
<L>And won &thorn;er wi&thorn;outen ende.</L>
<L>And alle &thorn;at were to mi consent,</L>
<L>Alle &thorn;ai hen to helle ywent,</L>
<L>Euer to liue [in pine] and wo.</L>
<L N="310">&THORN;erfore &thorn;ou art our alder fo".</L>
<L>Adam, &thorn;er he stode vp ri&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Bisou&yogh;t god ful of mi&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Deliuer out of his compeynie</L>
<L>&THORN;e fende &thorn;at hadde swiche envie</L>
<L N="315">To him and to his wiue Eue,</L>
<L>&THORN;at fonded so her soules to greue.</L>
<L>Adam, &thorn;er he stode al naked,</L>
<L>&THORN;o he hadde his preyer maked:</L>
<L>&THORN;urch &thorn;e pouwer of godes mi&yogh;t</L>
<L N="320">&THORN;e fende went out of hir si&yogh;t.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e sex and fourti days wer go</L>
<L>&THORN;at Adam hadde y&thorn;oled &thorn;at wo,</L>
<L>Out of &thorn;e water &thorn;o he cam.</L>
<L>&THORN;an seyd Eue to Adam:</L>
<L N="325">"Adam, Adam, wele is te,</L>
<L>And Adam, Adam, wo is me!</L>
<L>&THORN;ou hast &thorn;i penaunce to &thorn;ende brou&yogh;t:</L>
<L>&THORN;ou mi&yogh;t be ful glad in &thorn;ou&yogh;t;</L>
<L>And ich may sing allas allas,</L>
<L N="330">Icham wers &thorn;an ich was,</L>
<L>For now Ichaue eft agilt,</L>
<L>Se&thorn;&thorn;en we were out of paradis pilt.</L>
<L>&THORN;erfore Ichil now biginne</L>
<L>O&yogh;ain penaunce for to winne,</L>
<L N="335">And wende and won in &thorn;isternesse,</L>
<L>Out of alle li&yogh;tnesse;
<PB REF="00000149.tif" N="143"></L>
<L>&THORN;e foule flesche &thorn;at ha&thorn; agilt,</L>
<L>In &thorn;esternesse it schal be pilt".</L>
<L>Eue went fram Adam,</L>
<L N="340">In to &thorn;esternesse till &thorn;at sche cam;</L>
<L>And &thorn;o sche com to a &thorn;ester stede,</L>
<L>Ni&yogh;t and day in holy hede,</L>
<L>Gret wi&thorn; child, sche duelled &thorn;are,</L>
<L>In miche sorwe and michel care.</L>
<L N="345">&THORN;e time nei&yogh;ed atte last</L>
<L>&THORN;at Eue bigan to gret fast:</L>
<L>And hye bigan to gron sore</L>
<L>And seyd: "Louerd, merci, &thorn;ine ore!</L>
<L>Who may telle Adam mi &thorn;ou&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="350">In what sorwe &thorn;at ich am brou&yogh;t?</L>
<L>Y no haue messanger non</L>
<L>&THORN;at may on min eirand gon</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>"&amp; he sey&yogh;e me wi&thorn; his ey&yogh;e,</L>
<L>&amp; seyd: "Adam, &thorn;ou shalt dye.</L>
<L>Hold &thorn;at word in &thorn;i &thorn;ou&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="355">&amp; loke &thorn;ou for&yogh;ete it nou&yogh;t!"</L>
<L>&THORN;us seyd god almi&yogh;ti to me.</L>
<L>&THORN;o com ich in to er&thorn;e o&yogh;e,</L>
<L>&amp; liued in trauail &amp; in pine;</L>
<L>&amp; so schulen after al mine;</L>
<L N="360">Til god bicom man in er&thorn;e,</L>
<L>We schul haue penaunce &mdash; &amp; wele is wer&thorn;e:</L>
<L>For ich &amp; &thorn;i moder weren at asent</L>
<L>To breke godes comandment.</L>
<L N="365">For we haue him so agilt,</L>
<L>In our hertes he ha&thorn; ypilt</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e an euen &amp; a morwe</L>
<L>Sexti woundes of wo &amp; sorwe,</L>
<L>&THORN;at schal doure to alle mi blod".</L>
<L N="370">&amp; wi&thorn; &thorn;at word &thorn;er Adam stode</L>
<L>&amp; bigan to wepe sore</L>
<L>&amp; seyd: "merci, lord, &thorn;inore!</L>
<L>Lord &mdash; yblisced mot &thorn;ou wer&thorn;e! &mdash;</L>
<L>Wherto was y made of er&thorn;e</L>
<L N="375">Swiche pine here to dreye?</L>
<L>Wer time comen, ich wald dye!"</L>
<L>Of Adames sorwe Eue toke kepe</L>
<L>&amp; bigan bitter to wepe,</L>
<L>&amp; anon in &thorn;at ich stounde</L>
<L N="380">Sche kneled adoun on &thorn;e grounde</L>
