<L>Sore wepende, &amp; seyd &thorn;us:</L>
<L>"Lord, ich biseche &thorn;e,</L>
<L>Adames sorwe put in me!</L>
<L N="385">For al &thorn;e sorwe &thorn;at he is inne,</L>
<L>Is for mi gilt &amp; for mi sinne".</L>
<L>Adam hadde rew&thorn;e of his wiif,</L>
<L>&amp; was al ful of his liif,</L>
<L>&amp; seyd: "Eue, lat be &thorn;i fare,</L>
<L N="390">&amp; fond to bring me out of care!</L>
<L>Take Se&thorn; in &thorn;i compeynie,</L>
<L>&amp; lok &thorn;at &thorn;ou fast hey&yogh;e,</L>
<L>Lade him to paradise to &thorn;e &yogh;ate,</L>
<L>&amp; lat him abide &thorn;er ate</L>
<L N="395">&amp; let him stonden in &thorn;e si&yogh;t:</L>
<L>&amp; god, &thorn;at is ful of mi&yogh;t,</L>
<L>For he ha&thorn; nou&yogh;t trespast so miche</L>
<L>As haue we, sikerliche,</L>
<L>&THORN;erfore he may &thorn;e balder be</L>
<L N="400">To speke wi&thorn; Jhesu Crist, &thorn;an we".</L>
<L>Eue toke Se&thorn; anon,</L>
<L>&amp; dede hem in &thorn;e way, to gon.</L>
<L>Toward paradis anon &thorn;ai go.</L>
<L>&amp; &thorn;e fende, &thorn;at was her fo,</L>
<L N="405">Com &amp; mett wi&thorn; hem tvaye</L>
<L>Ri&yogh;t amid in &thorn;e waye,</L>
<L>&amp; bot Se&thorn; in &thorn;e visage:</L>
<L>&amp; afterward a gret stage</L>
<L>In his visage it was ysene,</L>
<L N="410">Where stoden his te&thorn; kene.</L>
<L>"Allas allas", qua&thorn; Eue &thorn;o,</L>
<L>"What icham curssed, &amp; o&thorn;er mo,</L>
<L>&THORN;at breken godes comandment!</L>
<L>Now is mi sones visage schent.</L>
<L N="415">Hadde we holden his hest ari&yogh;t,</L>
<L>&THORN;an hadde &thorn;e fende hadde no mi&yogh;t</L>
<L>For to touche nou&yogh;t of our blod,</L>
<L>No hadde ydon hem nou&yogh;t bot gode".</L>
<L>To &thorn;e fende &thorn;o seyd Eue.</L>
<L N="420">"Hou artow so hardi to greue</L>
<L>Godes creatour &thorn;at &thorn;urch his grace</L>
<L>Is fourmed after his owhen face?</L>
<L>Me &thorn;enke &thorn;at &thorn;ou dost nou&yogh;t ri&yogh;t</L>
<L>To wret&thorn;e wi&thorn; &thorn;e king of mi&yogh;t.</L>
<L N="425">Why artow so malicious
<PB REF="00000150.tif" N="144"></L>
<L>Toward god &amp; toward ous?"</L>
<L>&THORN;e fende answerd anon &thorn;is:</L>
<L>"Nou&yogh;t toward god our malice nis,</L>
<L>Bot toward &thorn;e &amp; al &thorn;e brod</L>
<L N="430">&THORN;at euer come&thorn; of &yogh;our blod:</L>
<L>For &thorn;urch &yogh;ou we ben ybrou&yogh;t<NOTE PLACE="foot">Ms. &thorn;urth st. &thorn;urch, wie 421, 439, 442, 455 u. &ouml;.; Laing liest &thorn;urch.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;er wo &amp; sinne is euer wrou&yogh;t.</L>
<L>&amp;, Eue, ichil &thorn;at &thorn;ou it wite:</L>
<L>Se&thorn;&thorn;en &thorn;ou &amp; Adam of &thorn;e appel bite,</L>
<L N="435">We haue hadde pouwer &amp; mi&yogh;t</L>
<L>To dere &yogh;ou bo&thorn;e day &amp; ni&yogh;t".</L>
<L>"A, foule &thorn;ing!" qua&thorn; Se&thorn;,</L>
<L>"Fro mi moder &thorn;at here ge&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot">L. l. heren.</NOTE></L>
<L>&amp; fro me, &thorn;urch godes mi&yogh;t</L>
<L N="440">Passe oway out of our si&yogh;t!"</L>
<L>&amp; &thorn;e fende, &thorn;e foule &thorn;ing,</L>
<L>&THORN;urch mi&yogh;t of &thorn;e heuen king</L>
<L>Out of her si&yogh;t oway he nam,</L>
<L>&THORN;ai nist neuer whar he bicam.</L>
<L N="445">Eue ha&thorn; Se&thorn; yladde</L>
<L>To paradys, as Adam badde.</L>
<L>&amp; Eue drou&yogh; hir fram &thorn;e &yogh;ate,</L>
<L>Sche no durst nou&yogh;t loke in &thorn;erate,</L>
<L>Sche durst nou&yogh;t schewe god hir face,</L>
<L N="450">Bot lete Se&thorn; abide grace.</L>
<L>&amp; Se&thorn; in &thorn;ilke stede,</L>
<L>Sore wepeand, in holy bede</L>
<L>He abod &thorn;er alle stille</L>
<L>Godes merci &amp; godes wille.</L>
<L N="455">&THORN;urch &thorn;e vertu of godes mi&yogh;t</L>
<L>&THORN;er com adoun an angel bri&yogh;t,</L>
<L>&amp; seyd to Se&thorn; in &thorn;is maner,</L>
<L>&THORN;at he mi&yogh;t wi&thorn; eren here:</L>
<L>"God, &thorn;at al &thorn;e warld ha&thorn; wrou&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="460">Sent &thorn;e word: &thorn;ou biddest for nou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Er &thorn;e term be ygon</L>
<L>Of fiue &thorn;ousende winter &amp; on</L>
<L>&amp; fiue &amp; tenti winter &amp; mo,</L>
<L>Er &thorn;at terme be ago</L>
<L N="465">&amp; god, &thorn;at is ful of mi&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Be in to er&thorn;e yli&yogh;t</L>
<L>&amp; haue ynomen kind of man</L>
<L>&amp; ba&thorn;ed in &thorn;e flom Jordan:</L>
<L>&THORN;an schal Adam &amp; Eue, his wiif,</L>
<L N="470">Be anoint wi&thorn; oyle of liif,</L>
<L>&amp; alle &thorn;o &thorn;at after hem comen</L>
<L>&THORN;at haue ciristendom ynomen.</L>
<L>Go tel Adam, &thorn;i fader, &thorn;is</L>
<L>&THORN;at no no&thorn;er grace &thorn;er nis.</L>
<L N="475">&amp; to gray&thorn;e him, bid him hey&yogh;e:</L>
<L>His terme nei&yogh;e&thorn; &thorn;at he schal dye.</L>
<L>&amp; when &thorn;e bodi, &thorn;at ha&thorn; don sinne,</L>
<L>&amp; &thorn;e soule schal parten atvinne,</L>
<L>Ri&yogh;t whan &thorn;at time schal be:</L>
<L N="480">Miche meruayl &yogh;e schullen yse &mdash;</L>
<L>So seyt mi lord, &thorn;at alle ha&thorn; wrou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>&amp; bidde&thorn; &thorn;at &yogh;e no drede nou&yogh;t</L>
<L>For nou&yogh;t &thorn;at &yogh;e schul here no se.</L>
<L>So he sent &yogh;ou word bi me".</L>
<L N="485">Eue &amp; Se&thorn; her way nome</L>
<L>&amp; went o&yogh;ain, as &thorn;ai come,</L>
<L>&amp; told Adam &thorn;e tiding</L>
<L>&THORN;at him sent &thorn;e heuen king.</L>
<L>&amp; Adam held vp bo&thorn;e his hond</L>
<L N="490">&amp; &thorn;onked god of alle his sond.</L>
<L>Adam his ei&yogh;en vnfeld:</L>
<L>&amp; se&thorn;&thorn;en his sone he biheld</L>
<L>&amp; seyd: "merci, swete Jhesus!</L>
<L>Who ha&thorn; wounded mi sone &thorn;us?"</L>
<L N="495">"Bi god! Adam", qua&thorn; Eue,</L>
<L>"He &thorn;at is about to greue</L>
<L>Oure soules, bo&thorn;e ni&yogh;t &amp; day,</L>
<L>As michel as euer he may;</L>
<L>&THORN;at is &thorn;e fende, &thorn;at is our fo,</L>
<L N="500">&THORN;at ha&thorn; ous brou&yogh;t in to &thorn;is wo:</L>
<L>He com &amp; mett wi&thorn; ous tvay,</L>
<L>As we &yogh;eden in &thorn;e way</L>
<L>&amp; went toward paradys:</L>
<L>&THORN;us he bot him in &thorn;e viis".</L>
<L N="505">"Owe, Eue!" qua&thorn; Adam &thorn;o,</L>
<L>"&THORN;ou hast ywrou&yogh;t michel wo!</L>
<L>Alle &thorn;at after ous be bore,</L>
<L>Alle schal curssen ous &thorn;er fore,</L>
<L>&amp; alle &thorn;at after ous liuen</L>
<L N="510">Bo&thorn;e amorwe &amp; eke aneuen</L>
<L>Schul be bisy to bere &thorn;e wo</L>
<L>&THORN;at is ywakened of ous tvo.</L>
<L>&THORN;erfore, Eue, telle alle &thorn;ine childer,</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e &thorn;e &yogh;onger &amp; &thorn;e elder:</L>
<L N="515">&THORN;at &thorn;ai be filed of our sinne;
<PB REF="00000151.tif" N="145"></L>
<L>&amp; bid hem ichon biginne</L>
<L>Ni&yogh;t &amp; day merci to crie.</L>
<L>Mi time is comen, y schal dye".</L>
<L>&THORN;us Adam bad Eue, his wiif,</L>
<L N="520">Techen his childer after his liif,</L>
<L>Hou &thorn;ai schuld anon biginne</L>
<L>To crien merci for her sinne.</L>
<L>&amp; &thorn;o he hadde ytau&yogh;t hem &thorn;us,</L>
<L>As &thorn;e boke telle&thorn; ous:</L>
